tachyon.client

Interface Cancelable

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    KeyValuePartitionWriter, KeyValueStoreWriter
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BufferedBlockOutStream, DummyFileOutputStream, FileOutStream, LineageFileOutStream, LocalBlockOutStream, OutStreamBase, RemoteBlockOutStream

    public interface Cancelable
    This interface should be implemented by all Tachyon output streams which support aborting the temporary data that has been written.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void cancel()
      Cancels the write to Tachyon storage.

    • Method Detail

      • cancel

        void cancel()
     throws IOException
        Cancels the write to Tachyon storage. This will delete all the temporary data and metadata that has been written to the worker(s). This method should be called when a write is aborted.
        Throws:
        IOException - if there is a failure when the worker invalidates the cache attempt
